                                <VBox prefHeight="146.0" prefWidth="394.0">
                                    <children>
                                        <Label alignment="CENTER" maxWidth="1.7976931348623157E308"
                                               text="~ Template Header ~" VBox.vgrow="NEVER">
                                            <font>
                                                <Font name="System Bold" size="12.0"/>
                                            </font>
                                        </Label>
                                        <TextArea fx:id="templateHeaderTextArea" maxHeight="1.7976931348623157E308"
                                                  maxWidth="1.7976931348623157E308" minHeight="0.0" minWidth="0.0"
                                                  prefHeight="200.0" prefWidth="200.0"
                                                  text="Hello! This is the header.&#10;&#10;This is usally a good place to put information which doesn't change between assignments,&#10;such as grading policy. I'm gonna use it to tell you about some features instead:&#10;&#10;Import a template (Feedback -&gt; Import Template), but not quite yet. It will replace&#10;what you're readining now.&#10;&#10;Import groups from folder structures&#10;    1. A single root folder is assumed to contain a single root folder per group. Any subfolders&#10;       of these top-level subfolders are considered group property.&#10;    2. Set file filters (e.g. *.java) to select the types of files to import.&#10;    3. Click done or close the window. The program will ask you if you want to clear old groups&#10;       or just import the new ones. Feedback will be created for each group, based on the template.&#10;&#10;Sick of writing the same thing over and over again?&#10;    1. Open the Pasta Editor (Ctrl+G) and click &quot;New Pasta&quot;&#10;    2. Create and add tags to organize items by content and by assignment.&#10;    3. Close the window. The program will ask if you want to use the new pasta.&#10;&#10;Quick insert (Pasta) at caret&#10;    1. Select a Pasta item (the search function is your friend) and select a position in a student file&#10;    2. Press (Ctrl+Q) or right-click the pasta list. The pasta will be pasted into&#10;       the student feedback referencing the current file and position.&#10;Some examples are included to let you try this out.&#10;&#10;When youre done, you can export everything as individual files using (Ctrl+E). You can also&#10;double-click (or right click) a group in the list to get a preview. Use the &quot;Toggle done&quot;&#10;function (CTRL+D) to keep track of your progress.&#10;"
                                                  VBox.vgrow="ALWAYS">
                                            <font>
                                                <Font name="Monospaced Regular" size="12.0"/>
                                            </font>
                                        </TextArea>
                                    </children>
                                </VBox>
                                <VBox prefHeight="200.0" prefWidth="100.0">
                                    <children>
                                        <Label alignment="CENTER" maxWidth="1.7976931348623157E308"
                                               text="~ Template Body ~" VBox.vgrow="NEVER">
                                            <font>
                                                <Font name="System Bold" size="12.0"/>
                                            </font>
                                        </Label>
                                        <TextArea fx:id="templateTextArea" maxHeight="1.7976931348623157E308"
                                                  maxWidth="1.7976931348623157E308" minHeight="0.0" minWidth="0.0"
                                                  prefHeight="200.0" prefWidth="200.0"
                                                  text="&#10;%HEADER%&#10;&#10;This is the body. There are a few tags you should know about:&#10;&#10;The %GROUP% tag simply indicates the name of the group being graded. It is the same&#10;as the values shown in the feedback lists.&#10;&#10;The %MANUAL% tag indicates that some text not to be exported as-is. For example,&#10;it may include code snippets that should be altered to fit the current group being&#10;graded. This is the ONLY tag which will not be removed when exporting.&#10;&#10;The %FILE: &lt;Filename&gt;% tag is special. It can be used to give feedback referencing an&#10;appropriate row and file (and column, if you like). If you did not use the automatic&#10;import function (Ctrl+I), files can be dragged-and-dropped onto the file view of a group&#10;to add it. &#10;&#10;About files:&#10;================================================================================&#10;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt; Main.java  &lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&#10;================================================================================&#10;%FILE:  Main.java  % &lt;-- This is a file tag. It's what the program actually looks for.&#10;&#10;This is what an automatic file section looks like (the width can be changed in the settings).&#10;It will be created the the bottom of the document if no footer tag is present. The tags&#10;are created automatically if they are not present when a file related function is used.&#10;&#10;&#10;%FOOTER%&#10;"
                                                  VBox.vgrow="ALWAYS">
                                            <font>
                                                <Font name="Monospaced Regular" size="12.0"/>
                                            </font>
                                        </TextArea>
                                    </children>
                                </VBox>
                                <VBox prefHeight="200.0" prefWidth="100.0">
                                    <children>
                                        <Label alignment="CENTER" maxWidth="1.7976931348623157E308"
                                               text="~ Template Footer ~" VBox.vgrow="NEVER">
                                            <font>
                                                <Font name="System Bold" size="12.0"/>
